==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Epiphora
<hw>E*piph"o*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<grk>'epifora`</grk>, fr. <grk>'epife`rein</grk> to bring to or upon;
<grk>'epi`</grk> + <grk>fe`rein</grk> to bring.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The watery eye; a disease in which the tears
accumulate in the eye, and trickle over the cheek.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>The emphatic repetition of a word
or phrase, at the end of several sentences or stanzas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epiphragm</ent>⟦br⟧
